result.formatted_address: 118-122 Tung Choi Street, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Ngan Lung Restaurant

reviews.text: Good service and the food is good. I had fried rice noodles with tea and milk. It was fairly good.
No surprises but still OK

No frills standard hk style 茶餐厅。。
A bit small space cramp though..
Not really baby friendly.
But food quick and good, and not ex.

It is slightly expensive for this kind of restaurant, but the slightly better-than-average taste balances things out. It has a clear English menu with photos of everything.  
I had beef tendon and belly with noodles. The beef was marinated in an ever-so-slightly spicy sauce, with some lettuce. Quite good. The milk tea was firmly in the "good" category. The noodle broth was not bad, but a little thin.
so far so good
